Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.95,0:00:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Father and mother were already \Na hair's breadth away from reconciling...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.41,0:00:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, suddenly, the very next moment, \Nmother returns to Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.43,0:00:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason was because Frau Gerlach had informed her \Nof receiving a proposal from the father of her children.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.17,0:00:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, just as things were finally \Nstarting to look up... Why?" -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.24,0:00:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise and Lotte indignantly \Ndemand an answer from their father. {/shout at dad}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.18,0:00:36.19,Sign,,0,0,110,,{\c&HE3FEFF&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 27 \N {\fs35} Two People, One Wish {/only one wish per two} {たったひとつの二人の願い} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.49,0:00:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after you parted, \Nmom was still attending your concerts for some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.08,0:00:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She knew your music comes from your heart, \Nso listening to it, she could feel and share your sorrow! {honest; frank; candid; straightforward}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.64,0:00:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus, it was just as painful to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.61,0:01:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.20,0:01:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd never think...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.25,0:01:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, answer honestly! \NDo you detest mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.43,0:01:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.76,0:01:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, I love her. \NI believe, she is a breathtaking woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.39,0:01:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom also once told me \Nmy dad is a breathtaking man!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.96,0:01:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe just a little bigheaded, featherbrained, too, \Nand with a naive soul! {good-natured person; credulous person; easy mark; simple soul; soft touch - I would assume this used in negative sense (think "dupe") as the rest of the adjectives here are rather negative}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.47,0:01:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Still an unknown composer, \Ntorturing the piano daily, to the point of exhaustion. {/obsessed with composing}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And mom would also offer a prayer daily \Nfor that passion to bear fruit!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.63,0:01:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were the happy times for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.06,0:01:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother was also my most devoted listener, \Nable to grasp my music thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.22,0:01:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just "was!" \NShe still is!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.83,0:01:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Last time I saw someone badmouthing your music, \Nmom threw a giant tantrum!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.16,0:01:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, your music \Nis a cornucopia of the most genuine kindness!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.10,0:02:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And that she hadn't met anyone \Nwho'd understand as much as she does!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.57,0:02:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it with my own eyes, \N during our time together -
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.48,0:02:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,mom still very much loves you, \Neven to this day!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.25,0:02:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So Herr Palfy is getting married?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.34,0:02:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You can imagine, what a reputation it would give him \Nto have his ex-wife hanging around at such a time. {to loiter; to drift; to hang about doing nothing; to wander aimlessly; to be restless}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.82,0:02:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I returned home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.52,0:02:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't plan on going to Vienna any time soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.53,0:02:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I've gotten quite used to living in Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.13,0:02:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Quarreling with our headstrong Editor is my true calling.  {/And if I don't constantly fight \Nour headstrong Editor, then who will?} {unsure what she means: without quarreling with ..., do my job}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.79,0:02:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about Lotte? What about Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.71,0:03:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What will become of those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they should go back \Nto where they belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.80,0:03:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte stays with me, \Nand Luise with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.84,0:03:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to separate them again? {to pull apart; to separate}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.81,0:03:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as the sisters had finally found each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after swapping places and everything \Nthey've been through, you'd still do that to them? {unsure: those girls, what kind of thoughts exchanged with each other, do you know? - maybe he means smt like "how they felt when they switched places" or w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I take great pity on those girls, \Nso it pains me just as much. {unsure, maybe she means "I do realize how miserable that'd make them"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.78,0:03:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I repent this one divorce \Nmore than anything else in my life. {lit: I've never regretted divrce as much as this time, but she's only been divorced once, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's too late now \Nto try and change anything. {/whatever you say}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.47,0:03:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. You really didn't have to hear all that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.88,0:03:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.99,0:03:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm all right now. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.76,0:04:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's return, then. {acutally he says something like "I'll give you a lift" but that's too heavy}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.46,0:04:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get home, make sure to call Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.13,0:04:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't let Lotte worry so much for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.14,0:04:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, call Munich now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.37,0:04:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Call and ask mom to come at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.64,0:04:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The four of us should live together, \Nthat would be the only fitting way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.41,0:04:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can well understand \Nhow you two feel about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.24,0:04:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this matter is for grown-ups to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.54,0:04:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In real life, things are never as simple as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.32,0:04:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.43,0:04:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish to be left alone \Nfor some while, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.10,0:04:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.73,0:04:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.28,0:04:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, spying is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.28,0:05:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? Palfy listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.22,0:05:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.65,0:05:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you see... The point is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.70,0:05:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just about to try dialing you myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.52,0:05:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world had happened? \NYou went home so abruptly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.27,0:05:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.26,0:05:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I remembered \Nabout a certain work that was due today. {/urgent}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.93,0:05:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in such a hurry, \Ncouldn't even drop by to bid my goodbyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.62,0:05:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And... How are girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.95,0:05:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They look restless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.62,0:05:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,On an unrelated note, \NI was told you're engaged now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.99,0:05:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.48,0:05:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Gerlach's beauty is truly striking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.46,0:05:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You met her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.39,0:05:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.97,0:05:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.12,0:05:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That was how she found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.49,0:05:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.77,0:06:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, actually, speaking of Frau Gerlach... Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.75,0:06:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also... considering a remarriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.91,0:06:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Remarriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.84,0:06:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With Editor-in-Chief Bernau, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.21,0:06:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.15,0:06:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I made up my mind \Non staying in Munich for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Congratulations to you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,For Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.83,0:06:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But... That's so out of the blue! \NMaybe she could, for just a little longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.60,0:06:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.24,0:06:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Your point is indisputable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.29,0:06:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.45,0:06:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.69,0:06:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it... What was it mom wanted to say? Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.73,0:06:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're kidding, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.41,0:07:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,For Lotte to return to Munich so soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Could mom ever say something like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.98,0:07:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"Everyone should return \Nto their usual lives as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.70,0:07:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Send her home tomorrow."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.92,0:07:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.08,0:07:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But..!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.35,0:07:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I protest! You can't just scatter \Nme and Lotte, like some pebbles! {to be dispersed; to get separated​}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.23,0:07:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This disobedience is unbefitting of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.04,0:07:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of your mother's feelings! {/that'd hurt ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.91,0:07:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hear this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.41,0:07:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't override the fact you two are sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.97,0:07:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, whenever you feel like \Nseeing each other, you'll have that freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.85,0:07:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.65,0:07:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be so callous?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.02,0:07:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.12,0:07:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.29,0:08:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.87,0:08:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.12,0:08:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It went completely south. {/didn't go well}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.71,0:08:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our cherished plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.78,0:08:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oath by the lake, in the Seebühl Village \Nis not getting fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.55,0:08:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, isn't there \Nanything we can still do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.25,0:08:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.80,0:08:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, I'll never be able to get along \Nwith a person such as Frau Gerlach!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.80,0:08:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.15,0:08:46.13,Sign,,0,0,0,,Gerlach Mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:09:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's highly unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.35,0:09:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My Irene is in the parlor until so late...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.48,0:09:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Palfy's record, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.42,0:09:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I've not been \Nlistening thoughtfully to it up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.37,0:09:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All I could see was his imposing figure, \Non a fuzzy background.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.31,0:09:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't that the most ordinary \Nfor someone truly in love?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.25,0:09:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But his music is quite the phenomenon indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.43,0:09:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Irene, you now have every right to hold your head high. {/you can be proud of this}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You're about to make this renowned genius yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.69,0:09:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, an artist's soul is inscrutable. {to us commoners,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.89,0:09:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, you'll be understanding enough \Nto shed light on it in your memoirs one day. {now, I'm amost certain it's actually にくい面もある but I'm not entirely sure what it's supposed to mean, usually it'd be "every cloud has a silver lining/everything has good and bad sides to it" but here, I don't see it neither bad nor good, whereas "nikui memoaru" actually makes just as much sense, especially that the word nikui itself has two opposite meanings, used sarcastically; overall lit is "those creatures called artists, for the sane people there are bad sides to having little understanding of them, too/for a commoner, it might be best to not understand him too much(this better aligns with Luiselotte's speech from before)"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.90,0:09:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Understanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.34,0:09:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing surpasses in importance \Nbeing understanding and caring towards your partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, I've been in love \Nwith only one half of Herr Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.70,0:10:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't be able to make him happy. {/I'm no match for her - usually anohito is used for men, so maybe it's "I won't make a good match for him"?; maybe it's not kanawanai at all; alt meaning is "cannot stand; cannot bear; cannot put up with; unbearable; intolerable​" so maybe she means the completely opposite thing here. I'm lost. Admitting defeat sounds nothing like gerlach, so I'd assume something like "I won't let them teach/shape me", but then two scenes later, she cancels the marriage so either it's "no match for her" after all or "I don't fit this man" but then again when did irene care about it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.49,0:10:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With Editor-in-Chief Bernau?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.14,0:10:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He definitely sounds like someone \Nable to make her happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.62,0:10:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NCan't get any sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.36,0:10:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.63,0:10:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only a short spell, \Nbut I enjoyed every second of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.31,0:10:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad really is my dad. \NOh, what a delight to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.70,0:10:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, I'll be practicing the piano \Nwith full devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.14,0:11:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So that next time we meet, \Nit won't leave you unimpressed! {/I'll receive your appraisal}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.08,0:11:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,See that you both treasure Luise, will you? {not a clue: you two should adore luise/you should dote on two luises - I don't suppose she means gerlach is going to love luise, right? maybe "with luise too, you'll both love my piano"} {to be affectionate to; to treat tenderly; to dote on; to show one's love (for); to cherish}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.78,0:11:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Luise will write me many happy letters about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.05,0:11:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can read those,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.26,0:11:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be as though dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.43,0:11:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As though dad is by my side, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.39,0:11:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll feel soothed... {I hate the way I hate to put this due to different word order, it sounds much more touching and expressive in japanese: when I read that, I too with dad, I too am together with dad, I have a feeling}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.23,0:11:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, promise me \Nyou won't send Luise away! {anywhere}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.40,0:11:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes without saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.97,0:11:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm never sending my Luise away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.34,0:11:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many years have passed, \NI will never forget my Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.84,0:11:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that you'll listen to it, \NI'll be composing the most ravishing music ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.48,0:11:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.09,0:11:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Lotte... \NWhy do I have to let you go? {hope he means this, tho itte may be "say" then I'm completely lost}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.95,0:12:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's very late now. Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.48,0:12:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night to you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.57,0:12:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How can a father be that foolish...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.81,0:12:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Inflicting such unthinkable suffering \Non his own children...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.38,0:12:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I made an unpardonable mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.44,0:12:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Need to talk to Irene immediately. {/meet}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.17,0:13:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Frau Irene,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.03,0:13:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, I must confer to you \Non a certain delicate matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.08,0:13:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to have a word with you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.71,0:13:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tolerate it, if my husband-to-be \Nis so indifferent to me, he doesn't even look my way. {/I want my husband-to-be to always look at me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.79,0:13:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You, however, have nothing but music in your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.50,0:13:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If things keep going in the current direction,\NI'm turning into a recluse as soon as we marry. {/it seems, when we marry, I'll always be left home for caretaking/house-watching/will have to give up on my worldly life}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.84,0:13:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is unthinkable!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.52,0:13:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I absolutely can't stand being neglected. {to leave alone; to leave as is; to ignore; to neglect}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.39,0:13:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, \NI can't stand children either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.93,0:13:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we're married, I was considering your daughter's \Nenrollment into a boarding school. {she doesnt say who is going to enroll so I'm not sure}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.37,0:13:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I had already informed Luise as well. {/proposed}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.49,0:13:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Or wait, was it the other one of the twins? {unsure what she means, maybe "should I prepare for two twins to enroll"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.27,0:13:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Irene, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.84,0:13:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. You'll never be able to bring yourself \Nto do something like that. {/You could never do such a thing/be in position. - not sure what she means, but I assume she bends the conversation into why they shouldn't marry}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.84,0:13:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been carried away by my fantasies \Nto even come up with such an idea. {/got obsessed/engrossed in my own dreams}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.75,0:14:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But then we come to a dead end. {still unsure, would assume "it's unrealistic/impossible dream" implying they'll never be able to come to terms}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.82,0:14:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was willing to marry you, \Nbut not your music. {I can't marry ... }
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.82,0:14:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us therefore pretend \Nthis promise was never made.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.13,0:14:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.03,0:14:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,, Frau Irene...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.53,0:14:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Irene, what is it you're saying to Herr Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.40,0:14:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be disheartened, Herr Palfy. {to be disappointed; to be dejected; to be downhearted; to be discouraged; to be disheartened; to lose heart; to feel let down​}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.34,0:14:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere out there, there's a place,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.34,0:14:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,where you, your music, and your child
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.31,0:14:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,would be altogether welcomed,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.12,0:14:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and sincerely loved
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.22,0:14:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by someone better. {lit: definitely, somewhere, you can come, where you music and child - all together will be loved by someone - I hate the wording on this, as always}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.69,0:14:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Irene...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.63,0:14:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A thousand pardons, Herr Palfy. \NI have a somewhat willful daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.29,0:14:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it was me who failed everyone. {/made a mistake/did unforgivable}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.53,0:14:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.69,0:15:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how it happened? \NYou two switched places?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.00,0:15:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But well, it sure is getting lonely here, \Nonce Lotte is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.77,0:15:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, my allegiance is unwavering - you'll find an ally in me, \Nno matter how many years pass. {/remember this/I'll remember it - not sure who remembers what} {/forever/anytime stay stay your ally}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Herr Gabele.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.73,0:15:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it? You never give up on hoping. {to throw away; to cast away; to dump; to discard}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.69,0:15:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,After whole seven years, \Nyou met with each other completely by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.63,0:15:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what they call fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.42,0:15:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Fate?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.72,0:15:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. A chance that God bestowed upon you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.05,0:15:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever obstacles you meet on your path, \Nthe key is to keep going. {/without giving up/if you're going through hell keep going}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.16,0:15:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, the God will be sure to reward you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.80,0:16:01.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,Vienna Western Station
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This past month feels like a dream already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.60,0:16:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that happened... \NI'll be sure to remember it for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.39,0:16:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, your bags are loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.34,0:16:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, you should wrap this up and board soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.13,0:16:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, I don't want to let you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.83,0:16:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise... Such a pity we can't be together \Neven on our birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.97,0:16:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Birthday?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.83,0:16:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right... Fourteenth of October. \NOnly three days left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.61,0:16:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it slipped my mind completely... {/I don't know how I didn't notice.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.51,0:16:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Lotte. \NI'll go get you a present after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.05,0:16:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Something you'd like?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.55,0:16:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing, already...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.84,0:16:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to be shy. Say it out loud. \NI'll grant anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.81,0:16:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Really {\i1}anything?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.76,0:16:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, anything at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.19,0:16:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I should compensate Lotte for seven years of waiting. {/saved up 7 years worth of gifts}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.80,0:17:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong! Luise has been waiting for this \Nfor seven years as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.66,0:17:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! \NI've been wanting it for seven years, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.90,0:17:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.61,0:17:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.71,0:17:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to have a dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.04,0:17:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to have a mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.56,0:17:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We want dad and mom \Nto start living together!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.62,0:17:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We want us four \Nto live all together!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.82,0:17:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking for such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.26,0:17:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's not something I can grant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.43,0:17:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For your mother, it's too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.67,0:17:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It can work, if you ask mom yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.67,0:17:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't need another birthday present ever again! {Book: Then you needn't ever give us a present again as long as we live! Not for birthdays and not for Christmas. Never at all!}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.17,0:17:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I would do without any presents for the rest of my life! \NNot even for Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.87,0:17:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, daddy! This is our last chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.28,0:17:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.41,0:17:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I beg you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.82,0:18:09.22,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munich Central Station
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.16,0:18:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.04,0:18:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back. Was the road tiring?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.33,0:18:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me carry this for you. \NSo, shall we head home?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.37,0:18:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, we're having your favorite, \Nsole meuniere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.71,0:18:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.71,0:18:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.45,0:18:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't have to come to Munich as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.98,0:18:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Does your father know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.93,0:19:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.02,0:19:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... I see you made sure \Nshe makes it here safely. Thank you. {lit: you sent to me - not specified who or how, so I assume she means "you even went as far as following her"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.74,0:19:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to marry you, Luiselotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.74,0:19:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.24,0:19:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you who I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.51,0:19:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Both me and my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.09,0:19:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this one moment... \NHow much had Luise and Lotte dreamt of it before!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.13,0:19:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Their father proposed a remarriage to their mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.77,0:19:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what would be the mother's answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.28,0:20:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Two tiny hearts are now beating so violently, \Nyou'd think they're trying to jump out. {/to the point of breaking}
Comment: 0,0:20:20.72,0:20:20.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.66,0:20:30.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.19,0:20:33.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.65,0:20:37.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.37,0:20:40.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.50,0:20:51.92,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.92,0:20:55.68,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.68,0:20:59.22,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.22,0:21:02.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.06,0:21:05.79,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.64,0:21:09.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.19,0:21:13.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.74,0:21:17.89,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.44,0:21:23.09,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.09,0:21:26.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.50,0:21:30.13,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.13,0:21:32.90,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.95,0:21:37.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.72,0:21:41.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:44.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.28,0:21:46.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.38,0:21:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad had finally made a proposal to mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.65,0:21:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"I love you, and I want to marry you."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.09,0:21:57.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,Had he really only realized it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.83,0:21:59.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,But now, we're all living together!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.56,0:22:01.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,And we're the happiest family ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.30,0:22:03.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,They say, "Lotte, you're just like your dad!" {no clue what it means, surely not the appearances?}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.32,0:22:07.49,Sign,,0,0,0,,And mom's face is all wrinkled from crying! {crumpled; rumpled; wrinkled; creased; tousled; disheveled; dishevelled}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.49,0:22:09.90,Sign,,0,0,0,,But overall, we've never been happier!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.90,0:22:11.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next time, I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.74,0:22:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Best Birthday Ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.74,0:22:16.04,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 28 \N Best Birthday Ever {最高の誕生日}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.41,0:22:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
